    "name": "COU1: Tibial plateau stress prediction for TKA implant system (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite-element model is used to predict peak von Mises stress and contact pressure at the bone-implant interface of a total knee arthroplasty tibial component under physiological gait loading. Model influence is MODERATE (model supplements bench testing and informs design iteration); decision consequence is MODERATE (incorrect prediction could lead to suboptimal implant geometry but device is Class II with established predicate). Model Risk Level 3 per the Nagaraja framework.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FE analysis to predict peak tibial plateau stress and contact pressure distributions across five representative gait-cycle load cases for a Class II TKA tibial component. Results are used to confirm that peak stress remains below cortical bone fatigue threshold and to guide tray geometry optimization. Uncertainty quantification via Monte Carlo on cortical and cancellous bone moduli.",
    "modelInfluence": "Moderate",
    "decisionConsequence": "Moderate",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
